  "response_text": "**Median of Two Sorted Arrays Algorithm**\n=====================================\n\nThe problem of finding the median of two sorted arrays can be solved efficiently using a binary search approach. This algorithm has a time complexity of O(log(min(m, n)), where m and n are the sizes of the two input arrays.\n\n**Algorithm Description**\n------------------------\n\nThe algorithm works by finding the partition point in the two arrays such that the elements on the left side of the partition point in both arrays are less than or equal to the elements on the right side. The median is then the average of the elements at the partition points in the two arrays.\n\n**Code Implementation**\n----------------------\n\nHere is a Python implementation of the algorithm:\n```python\ndef find_median_sorted_arrays(nums1, nums2):\n    \"\"\"\n    Find the median of two sorted arrays.\n\n    Args:\n        nums1 (list): The first sorted array.\n        nums2 (list): The second sorted array.\n\n    Returns:\n        float: The median of the two arrays.\n",
